First, 0.2 g of prepared MIL-Cr was dispersed in 7 mL DW. Following that, a specific volume (0.5, 1, 2, and 3 mL) of 0.02 g/mL N-CQDs solution was poured into the mixture and stirred at ambient temperature for 17 h. The product (recorded as MIL-Cr/N-CQDs(x), where × denotes the N-CQDs volume added) was centrifuged and washed five times with DW. Finally, the obtained product was activated in a vacuum oven at 100 °C for 5 h. Scheme 1
                         illustrates the steps of MIL-Cr/N-CQDs preparation. See (Scheme 2
                        ).
